        "text_A6jABR": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Emmanuela Aba Graham is a Toronto-based industrial designer who explores the intersection of identity and form through pattern-making. Drawing from her Ghanaian-Canadian heritage, Graham creates garments that challenge conventional silhouettes while honoring the complexity of feminine identity.</p><p>Her work is characterized by a sophisticatd tension between structure and ease. This duality stands at the core of Graham's design philosophy, offering wearers both freedom and power through carefully engineered garments. </p><p>Each collection presents a conceptual narrative, inviting wearers to participate in an ongoing dialogue about presentation, perception, and presence.</p>"
